data.meta_description: Yearbook 2022 Complete II Compressed - Free ebook download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read book online for free. The English Chess Federation 2022 Yearbook provides a summary of the organization's activities over the past year. Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, much of the Federation's work shifted online, growing its online club membership to over 7,000 players and hosting numerous online tournaments. Planning is underway to restart over-the-board events like the British Chess Championships in a hybrid format. The Federation also supported clubs, developed coaching resources, and worked to improve membership benefits during this challenging time for chess in England.
